<div id='sib_body'>
  <center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="2" width="580" summary="form">
   <tr>
    <td align="left">
     <center>
      <h2>Pretty Printing and Shading of Multiple-Alignment files<br/></h2>
     </center>
     <h3>This server uses version 3.21 of BOXSHADE, written by K. Hofmann and M. Baron. <a href="/software/BOX_doc.html">BOXSHADE</a> is in the public domain and available from Source Forge  <a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/boxshade/">http://sourceforge.net/projects/boxshade/</a></h3>
     <h3>This <strong>server</strong> takes a multiple-alignment file in either GCG's MSF-format or Clustal ALN-format.<br/>
     Output can be created in the following formats:</h3>
     <ul>
      <li>
        <h3>Postscript/EPS (using shaded background)</h3>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>RTF old (using colors)</h3>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>RTF new (using shaded background)</h3>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>XFIG-files (using shaded background)</h3>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>ASCII (showing similarities)</h3>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>ASCII (showing differences)</h3>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>HPGL (using colors)</h3>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>PICT (for later editing on MACs and PCs)</h3>
      </li>
      </ul>
       <h3>
       If you have problems using this server (like getting no result), <a href="/software/BOX_error.html">read this</a> and see the <a href="/software/BOX_faq.html">FAQ list</a>.
     </h3>
     <form method="post" action="/cgi-bin/BOX_form_parser">
     <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="2" width="580" summary="BOXshade submit form">
      <tr>
       <td bgcolor="#d3d3d3">
        <div align="right">
         <h3>Output format</h3>
         <h3>Font Size</h3>
         <h3>Consensus Line</h3>
        </div>
       </td>
       <td bgcolor="#d3d3d3">
        <h3><select name="outp" size="1">
         <option selected="selected" value="Postscript_portrait">Postscript_portrait</option>
